data.title: Algeria
data.meta_description: Rock art in the caves of Tassili n’Ajjer in southeastern Algeria date from at least 10,000 BC, pointing to Neolithic settlements and domesticated herds in a savannah landscape quite different from the present desert. The original inhabitants were probably...
